depositAndSend(uint256,(uint32,bytes32,u.details: LOCAL ONLY: For users on hub chain wanting to deposit + bridge  Flow: WLFI  Vault  vEAGLE  Wrapper  EAGLE  Bridge

depositAndWrap(uint256,address).details: LOCAL ONLY: For users on hub chain HIDDEN STEPS:      1. Transfer WLFI from user      2. Deposit WLFI to vault  get vault shares (HIDDEN!)      3. Wrap vault shares  get EAGLE OFT      4. Transfer EAGLE to user USER SEES:      WLFI in  EAGLE out

handleCompose(address,bytes32,bytes,uint.details: Called by lzCompose in try-catch for automatic refunds

lzCompose(address,bytes32,bytes,address,.details: Called by endpoint when tokens arrive with composeMsg  AUTOMATIC OPERATION DETECTION: - If caller is ASSET_OFT  deposit flow - If caller is SHARE_OFT  redeem flow

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

redeemAndSend(uint256,(uint32,bytes32,ui.details: LOCAL ONLY: For users on hub chain wanting to redeem + bridge  Flow: EAGLE  Wrapper  vEAGLE  Vault  WLFI  Bridge

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setDelegate(address).details: Only the owner/admin of the OApp can call this function.Provides the ability for a delegate to set configs, on behalf of the OApp, directly on the Endpoint contract.

params._delegate: The address of the delegate to be set.

setPeer(uint32,bytes32).details: Only the owner/admin of the OApp can call this function.Indicates that the peer is trusted to send LayerZero messages to this OApp.Set this to bytes32(0) to remove the peer address.Peer is a bytes32 to accommodate non-evm chains.

params._peer: The address of the peer to be associated with the corresponding endpoint.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

unwrapAndRedeem(uint256,address).details: LOCAL ONLY: For users on hub chain HIDDEN STEPS:      1. Transfer EAGLE from user      2. Unwrap EAGLE  get vault shares (HIDDEN!)      3. Redeem vault shares  get WLFI      4. Transfer WLFI to user USER SEES:      EAGLE in  WLFI out

ASSET_OFT().notice: The asset OFT for cross-chain asset transfers (WLFI/USD1)

REGISTRY().notice: EagleRegistry for endpoint and chain info

SHARE_OFT().notice: The share OFT for cross-chain share transfers (EAGLE)

WRAPPER().notice: The vault wrapper for share conversion

depositAndSend(uint256,(uint32,bytes32,u.notice: Deposit assets and send shares cross-chain

depositAndWrap(uint256,address).notice: Deposit WLFI/USD1 and receive EAGLE in ONE transaction

endpoint().notice: Retrieves the LayerZero endpoint associated with the OApp.

getContracts().notice: Get all contract addresses for UI integration

handleCompose(address,bytes32,bytes,uint.notice: Handle compose operations with vault + wrapper integration

peers(uint32).notice: Retrieves the peer (OApp) associated with a corresponding endpoint.

previewDepositAndWrap(uint256).notice: Preview how much EAGLE you'll get for depositing WLFI

previewUnwrapAndRedeem(uint256).notice: Preview how much WLFI you'll get for redeeming EAGLE

redeemAndSend(uint256,(uint32,bytes32,ui.notice: Redeem shares and send assets cross-chain

setDelegate(address).notice: Sets the delegate address for the OApp.

setPeer(uint32,bytes32).notice: Sets the peer address (OApp instance) for a corresponding endpoint.
